author: @lada.violin
text:
TTT is not a good choice for a new carat since it's hard to remember everyone and it's important who is who there. Also the editing is fast and you need to understand a lot in a short time, and the family-like atmosphere is not that welcoming when you're not acquainted to the members yet. I would recommend sub-unit, sports, or something very easy to understand for start. Mafia, for example, is a game that is common for most countries and doesn't require additional explanation.

Best to learn might be cuts from some episodes that you yourself find the best!
SVT's got talent is a good one to remember everyone one by one.
ì¶œë°œ is not very clear but fun enough to not care about it.
Bad Clue is also one that can immerse someone quickly.

I had a period of adaptation to GoSe, because my Korean is weak, subtitles are fast and you might need to pause a lot, miss some content while trying to understand the ongoing situation, replay to get both the picture and its meaning. Lots of jokes are based on pure Korean puns or are just cut so fast mid-sentence it's even hard to capture the screen with subs. Or both. A lot of local Korean games are not easy to follow by a foreigner, some food, some ethics are not as obvious for us and need time to comprehend. I rewatched GoSe and caught a bit more than before, mostly 'cause I just got used to members and Korean culture, but I know I'm not getting the fullest picture yet (this plays a big part in TTT, where watching the video and getting the message through subs is more difficult, since the message is more diverse and hard to guess from the context, you always are reading and not getting to see what's actually going on - unless you rewind every few minutes).
Sorry for the long comment heh(: 
I like Going Seventeen a lot, and know a bit about introducing it to people who don't know SVT or Korean, so I decided to share most common difficulties and my top best choices to share first!

author: @bravennn
text:
GoSe is not just a variety show. I want you to know what feeling it shares to people and how important this show is to us, viewers. Every GoSe episode makes me reminisce the moments me and my friends had when we were young. And when we started working +  the pandemic happen, it's hard to play like we used to, but GoSe makes me remember and makes me hold on to our precious memories and the memories that we can create in the future. 

Actually, when we had our get together for new year's celebration, we played the games I can remember from GoSe and it's really fun. I didn't expected them to like mafia game that much and even said to do it on our next get together. I'm so thankful for the happiness and remembrance GoSe gives me. It makes me want to meet my friends more often.

author: @hopeworld5869
text:
I'm proud to be a Carat! The boys always work so hard to give us the best content. Going Seventeen is seriously my favorite variety show. I'm always looking forward to the episode to watch what amazing content they came up too. They're not comedians but they are so effortlessly funny. The chemistry all the members have with each other is the best. Of course they fight and argue but that's what you do even with the closest person. It's because they're close like family that they're able to talk it out, reconcile, get stronger and move on together. For me, they have the best and healthiest vibe of all the groups I stan and I think that it's pretty impressive for a group of 13 members. They've come a long way and I wish with all my heart even after the group stop promoting, that they will always be there for each other no matter what ğŸ’™ğŸ’™ğŸ’™
P.S. Special mention to all the staffs! Always being the scene, they worked hard, took care of the boys and helped them becoming the group that they are today. Even without knowing them, I'm grateful to every single one of them. Thank you!!

Going Seventeen is indeed a healing program. After a busy week, I always look forward to Wednesdays because I know it will be another fun episode. I applaud all the members and the staff behind this content. We started with less than a million views and now we achieved almost a billion views and that's a legend. People, either CARAT or CUBIC, are watching this because of the wittiness of the members. Even other groups mentioned watching this because they are fun to watch and that's thanks to the chemistry between the members. Their passion and love for CARATS made this content a legend that even other groups tried to copy but they just can't. SEVENTEEN set the standard of the idol-variety show and that's because of their love to their fans. 2022 will be another year of legendary episodes and I wish for their health more than anything else.

To all CARATS like me, let's make this a year full of fun and positiveness because the members deserved it all.

author: @winwinsonlylinesinboss
text:
I feel like what I love the best about SEVENTEEN is that they're the same in almost every aspect. In 2012, they were these trainees that livestreamed their day and they still managed to be funny and have sweet moments. Some of their most iconic moments can be pulled from this era of 2012-2014 when they were livestreaming. Their natural comedy comes from their chemistry with each other. It was obvious back then, and it's even stronger today with them knowing each other for over a decade. 

Whether you watched them in 2012 when they were trainees, in 2015 when they debuted, 2017 when Going Seventeen started, 2019 when they went on knowing bros and they all got variety show gigs, 2020 when Going Seventeen got INSANELY popular outside of Carats, or in 2021, they are still mostly the same people. 

They remind us every time they film, whether they do it intentionally or not. Everything they are is something that was built upon by things they've shown in the past. Almost every part of their journey as idols has been documented by the internet. It's something incredible that we can see how they grew up every step of the way. But it's even more incredible to see how much they've stayed the same despite growing up. 

Just like their discography, Going Seventeen is very diverse with all types of genres. It's just so cool that they can be all of these things at once. They're ALL amazing singers, dancers, rappers, performers, comedians, hard workers, insanely dedicated, insanely determined, professional, intelligent, talented, strong, bright young men. It's amazing what they're capable of as a group, but they have even more skills individually. They're all amazing and this isn't just me trying to over-hype them, they're all genuinely talented people. They have worked hard for everything they have, and it always inspires me to keep going because it WILL be worth it. 


I really do love GoSe, and I hope it will continue for many years. Even when SEVENTEEN get older, I will always love watching them as comedians and listening to them as musicians. 

Blah blah sappy time over, I do have a tip for Cubics who want to know more SEVENTEEN and baby Carats, the BEST way to watch Going Seventeen is watching all of their really old content until now. You bet that SEVENTEEN jokes a lot about the old stuff they have filmed. One example is One Fine Day in Yeoseodo Season 1 aka the 13 Castaways. They filmed it in 2015 and it's very iconic. They mention this one a lot particularly because it really did shape them as people lol Things like S.Coups chopping wood, Kwon Fire (hoshi lol), the whole swinging fire thing lmaoo 

Not to mention, a lot of episodes mention things about things they've said on Weverse or the Weverse Magazine. things that are bound to be lost in translation later in the future, but they're fun facts. Not to mention their Vlives. A lot of Vlives. SEVENTEEN film a lot lol, it's overwhelming, but I love it. There's always more stuff to watch, so it's never boring.

text:
i think *going seventeen* will transcend time.

carats and cubics know the thrill of watching the episodes after being uploaded and gets the thrill of waiting for the next episode. there are also new-born carats like me who have started watching mid 2021 and basically scrolls through episodes that were already on a youtube playlist. there will also be future generations of carats and cubics who will discover going seventeen for the first time and will fall in love with the series and will be thrilled while waiting for more.

whichever era you started watching gose, it will still give you the same feelings â€“ the warmth of seventeen's laughter, the mixed fear and fun in horror themed episodes, the excitement of their adventures, and most importantly the feeling of love. love of the members for each other, the love and support of carats, cubics and the staff for seventeen, and the love that emanates from each episode that aims to reach every person, fan or not, and fill their days with laughter and help ease their stresses away.

discovering seventeen in 2021, watching gose from the earlier ones up to the present, and stanning them ever since has been the best decisions i think i've ever made.

all the best to svt and GoSe staffs!
